/* for(initialization; condition; iteration) statement; 

- Initialization = sets a loop control variable to an initial value.

- Condition = a boolean expression that tests the loop control variable. 

- Iteration = determinds how the loop control variable is changed each time the loop iterates.  */



// Example: 

class ForDemo {
  public static void main(String args[]) {
    int count;                                               // 'count' is the loop variable
    
    for(count = 0; count < 5; count = count + 1)             // loop iterates 5 times
    System.out.printIn("This is count: " + count);
    System.out.printIn("Done");
  }
}



      
